			<h2><a href="http://www.dorkbot.org/dorkbotbristol/?p=51" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Audio Symposium">Audio Symposium</a></h2>
			<h4>May 8th, 2007<!-- by Clare --> &middot; <a href="http://www.dorkbot.org/dorkbotbristol/?p=51#respond" title="Comment on Audio Symposium">No Comments</a></h4>
			<div class="entry">
				<p>Bath Spa University School of Music and Performing Arts presents:</p>
<p>The Realtime AudioMedia group annual Practice-led Research Symposium</p>
<p>Saturday May 19th, 10:30 – 5:00, The Michael Tippett Centre, Newton Park, nr. Bath.</p>
<p>Admission FREE, Refreshments provided</p>
<p>Speakers:</p>
<p>Trevor Wishart (University of Durham) – sound transformation and computer processing</p>
<p>Alistair MacDonald (Royal Scottish Academy of Music and Drama) – ‘the sensuous and the invisible’ - collaborative installation/interactive work with Carol Brown, Sarah Rubidge and others</p>
<p>Bret Battey (DeMontfort University) – ‘visual music’ – historical context and current practice</p>
<p>Andy Keep - The behaviour of electronic feedback</p>
<p>Jan Meinema - sound and phenomenology - relating philosophical notions on experiencing sound to sound design practice (film sound / sound installation).</p>
<p>Joseph Hyde – live audiovisual performance</p>
<p>Chrissie Harrington – ‘architecting the body’ – interfaces between the body, architecture and digital media</p>
<p>For more information or to reserve a place, please email Joseph Hyde:<br />
j.hyde@bathspa.ac.uk</p>
<br /><div class='pLink'><a href="http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php" onclick="javascript:urchinTracker('/outbound/www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?ref=/dorkbotbristol/index.php?paged=5'); window.open('http://www.addthis.com/bookmark.php?pub=&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.dorkbot.org%2Fdorkbotbristol%2F%3Fp%3D51&amp;title=Audio+Symposium', 'addthis', 'scrollbars=yes,menubar=no,width=620,height=520,resizable=yes,toolbar=no,location=no,status=no'); return false;" title="Bookmark using any bookmark manager!" rel="external"><img src="http://s3.addthis.com/button1-bm.gif" alt="Social Bookmarking Tool"/></a></div>			</div>	
